inition (PlatformIO) or the ESP-IDF default decides. **Warning: specifying a mode your flash chip does not support will cause the ESP32 to fail to boot.**","options":[{"label":"qio","value":"qio"},{"label":"qout","value":"qout"},{"label":"dio","value":"dio"},{"label":"dout","value":"dout"},{"label":"opi","value":"opi"}],"display_format":null,"advanced":true,"help_link":"https://esphome.io/components/esp32#configuration-variables"},{"key":"flash_size","type":"string","label":"Flash Size","description":"The amount of flash memory available on the ESP32 board/module. One of `2MB`, `4MB`, `8MB`, `16MB` or `32MB`. Defaults to `4MB`. **Warning: specifying a size larger than that available on your board will cause the ESP32 to fail to boot.**","default_value":"4MB","options":[{"label":"2MB","value":"2MB"},{"label":"4MB","value":"4MB"},{"label":"8MB","value":"8MB"},{"label":"16MB","value":"16MB"},{"label":"32MB","value":"32MB"}],"display_format":null,"advanced":true,"help_link":"https://esphome.io/components/esp32#configuration-variables"},{"key":"partitions","type":"nested","label":"Partitions","description":"A partition table CSV file or a list of custom partitions to add. See [Partitions](https://esphome.io/components/esp32#esp32-partitions).","display_format":null,"multi_value":true,"advanced":true,"help_link":"https://esphome.io/components/esp32#configuration-variables","config_entries":[{"key":"type","type":"integer","label":"Type","required":true,"display_format":null,"advanced":true},{"key":"name","type":"string","label":"Name","required":true,"display_format":null,"advanced":true},{"key":"size","type":"integer","label":"Size","required":true,"display_format":null,"advanced":true},{"key":"subtype","type":"integer","label":"Subtype","required":true,"display_format":null,"advanced":true}]},{"key":"toolchain","type":"string","label":"Toolchain","description":"Toolchain used to build the firmware.","display_format":null,"advanced":true,"help_link":"https://esphome.io/components/esp32#configuration-variables"},{"key":"watchdog_timeout","type":"time_period","label":"Watchdog Timeout","description":"The timeout applied to the ESP-IDF task watchdog. If a subscribed task fails to feed the watchdog within this period, the device will reboot. Useful for power-managed devices or long blocking operations that need extended watchdog windows. Defaults to `5s`, valid range is `5s` to `60s`. Note: OTA updates temporarily raise the watchdog to `15s` when the configured timeout is below that threshold.","default_value":"5s","display_format":null,"advanced":true,"help_link":"https://esphome.io/components/esp32#configuration-variables"}],"required_groups":[{"kind":"at_least_one","keys":["board","variant"]}]}
